============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Alzheimer's
Type:        Neurological
Pathogen:    Non-communicable
Transmission:Aging/genetics
Symptoms:    Memory loss, confusion
Treatment:   No cure; slowing medications
Deaths/yr:   0.12M
Vaccine:     No
Discovered:  1906

Disease:     Dengue
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Dengue virus
Transmission:Aedes mosquito
Symptoms:    Fever, severe joint pain, rash
Treatment:   Supportive care, fluids
Deaths/yr:   0.04M
Vaccine:     Yes (for previously infected)
Discovered:  1779

Disease:     Malaria
Type:        Parasitic
Pathogen:    Plasmodium falciparum
Transmission:Mosquito bite
Symptoms:    Fever, chills, sweating cycles
Treatment:   Artemisinin combination therapy
Deaths/yr:   0.619M
Vaccine:     Yes (RTS,S approved 2021)
Discovered:  1880

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Four Color Theorem
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      Any planar map needs at most 4 colors
Applications: Cartography, graph coloring
Discoverer:   Appel and Haken (1976)

Theorem/Law:  Binomial Theorem
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      (a+b)^n = sum of C(n,k) a^k b^(n-k)
Applications: Probability, statistics, polynomial algebra
Discoverer:   Newton/Pascal (1665)

Theorem/Law:  Nash Equilibrium
Branch:       Game Theory
Formula:      No player benefits from unilateral strategy change
Applications: Economics, AI, political science
Discoverer:   John Nash (1950)

